# Autostart configuration for LXDE-pi (Legacy LXDE)
# This file is placed in: ~/.config/lxsession/LXDE-pi/autostart
# Lines starting with @ are autostart entries

# Launch desktop file manager
@pcmanfm --desktop --profile LXDE-pi

# Disable screen blanking and power management
@xset s off
@xset -dpms
@xset s noblank

# Start the Chromium kiosk setup
# Note: Adjust the username in the path if different from 'pi'
@/home/pi/chromium-autostart.sh